HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - RUSSIA (ROSTOV, STAVROPOL)
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Crimean-Congo hem. fever - Kazakhstan (south) 990506155836
Crimean-Congo hem. fever - Russia (south) 990703125637
[1
Date: Wed 21 Jul 1999
From: Alexander Vladyko, ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for the NIS/CIS
Via: Tatjana A. Ablova <ata@ns.briem.ac.by>

To my knowlege and from the newspapers (the scientific communications are
absent) 136 people have been hospitalized in the Rostov region and 6 of them
have died.
Of these people only 65 had clinical symptoms similar to Crimean-Congo
hemorrhagic fever [CCHF (from words on TV of Gennadij Onischenko, the
First Deputy Minister of the Russian Health Ministry).
I have rung colleagues in Russia on cause of this outbreak and it is clear
that diagnosis of CCHF isn't yet confirmed.
Professor Elena Leschinskaya, one of the main Russian health authorities,
confirms that the clinical picture of the disease is not typical for either
CCHF, enteroviruses, tick-borne encephalitis or any respiratory infections
(quoted in "Izvestiya" newspaper, 20 Jul 1999).
Regrettably, in spite of several attempts to get further information from
the other Russian health authorities on this outbreak, I have not been able
to get any sort of confirmation so far. It was impossible, in particularl,
to obtain confirmation on any samples taken for investigation from either
patients or dead persons.
I think that I will be able to obtain more exact information in 1-2 months,
when data on this outbreak will be published in Russian specialized journals
and bulletins, for example, the Russian "Public Health and the Environment"
bulletin.
Essential intermediate information I shall report in addition.
--
Alexander Vladyko
<ata@ns.briem.ac.by>
[We thank Alex for his efforts - Mod.JW
